Reports say that Federal Government has applied to the Federal High Court in Abuja for an order of temporary forfeiture of about 22 properties allegedly owned by Deputy Senate President Ike Ekweremadu. According to the Nation, the houses are located in Abuja, London, the United States and Dubai, United Arab Emirates. Those in Abuja •No. 11, Evans Enwerem Street, Apo Legislative Quarters, Apo, Abuja.
•Plot 2633 Kyami, Abuja.
•Housing Estate (Plot 1106 CRD, Cadastral Zone 07-07, Lugbe, Abuja.
•Plot 2782 Asokoro Extension, Abuja.
•Houses at Citi Park Estate, Gwagwalada, Abuja.
•Plot 1474 Cadastral Zone BD6, Mabushi, Abuja.
•Congress Court, Abuja.
•Flat 1, Block D25, Athletics Street, (24th Street) Games Village, Abuja.
•Plot 66, 64 Crescent, Gwarimpa Estate, Abuja.
Those in London
•Flat 4 Varsity Court, Harmer Street, WIH 4NW, London.
